name: Roanoke City and Alleghany Health District
tweet: I’ve got you covered!  Wearing a face covering helps protect others. Cloth face coverings slow the spread of COVID-19. They can be made from household items, such as a piece of cloth and rubber bands, a bandana, or a scarf. #IveGotYouCovered. Let us know who you cover for!  https://t.co/icPdpq4xnd

name: Roanoke City and Alleghany Health District
tweet: Join the movement - remind others that covering your face when you have to go out in public protects those around you. Take a selfie in your face covering, use the hashtag #IveGotYouCovered, and tag a friend you cover for.  https://t.co/mfLS7Gfv9F

tweet: If you feel sick, try to stay away from everyone else in the house. If you have to be near them, wear a cloth mask, a scarf, or a scarf to cover your nose and mouth.
